works.description: A few minutes back, Royal bride Kate Middleton stepped out of the Rolls Royce Phantom VI Landaulet and entered the Westminster Abbey. Her wedding dress was a big mystery and now, it’s been revealed. Sarah Burton at Alexander McQueen has designed the wedding dress, which is an ivory gown with lace applique floral detail. The train of the dress measures just 2.7 meters. There is no word yet on the actual price of Kate’s wedding dress. The skirt was handmade by the royal school of needlework at Hampton Court.
